1
00:00:06,206 --> 00:00:08,976
(gasping)

2
00:00:08,976 --> 00:00:10,777
Hey there, Kai!

3
00:00:10,777 --> 00:00:12,246
Huh?

4
00:00:12,246 --> 00:00:13,580
Sorry?

5
00:00:13,580 --> 00:00:16,083
Uh, oh, I‐‐

6
00:00:16,083 --> 00:00:18,519
My mistake, you look
like a friend of mine.

7
00:00:18,519 --> 00:00:20,287
(sighing)

8
00:00:20,287 --> 00:00:22,422
Well, look who it is!

9
00:00:22,422 --> 00:00:23,924
Hey, Shin.

10
00:00:25,325 --> 00:00:28,161
(meowing)

11
00:00:28,161 --> 00:00:33,500
♪

12
00:00:33,500 --> 00:00:36,436
♪ Vanguard, well
it's not a lie ♪

13
00:00:36,436 --> 00:00:39,406
♪ This legend will
be starting now ♪

14
00:00:39,406 --> 00:00:45,646
♪ To the future, just
lead us all the way ♪

15
00:00:45,646 --> 00:00:48,148
♪

16
00:00:48,148 --> 00:00:49,449
♪ Go! ♪

17
00:00:49,449 --> 00:00:54,588
♪

18
00:00:54,588 --> 00:01:00,294
♪ We can't hold back this
feeling just any longer ♪

19
00:01:00,294 --> 00:01:03,297
♪ Come on, tear off
everything you've got ♪

20
00:01:03,297 --> 00:01:06,099
‐♪ Get crazy way ♪
‐♪ Get crazy way ♪

21
00:01:06,099 --> 00:01:08,068
♪ There's no stopping,
there's no running ♪

22
00:01:08,068 --> 00:01:11,838
♪ I can hear his voice
calling for me somewhere ♪

23
00:01:11,838 --> 00:01:14,408
♪ I'll cross the bridge,
a head‐on battle now ♪

24
00:01:14,408 --> 00:01:15,642
‐♪ Here we go ♪
‐♪ Here we go ♪

25
00:01:15,642 --> 00:01:17,844
‐♪ Hurry up ♪
‐♪ Hurry up ♪

26
00:01:17,844 --> 00:01:20,747
♪ Nobody's gonna
ever interfere ♪

27
00:01:20,747 --> 00:01:23,016
♪ 3, 2, 1, let's go! ♪

28
00:01:23,016 --> 00:01:26,820
♪ Vanguard, an image
comes rising from deep

29
00:01:26,820 --> 00:01:29,156
within our souls, yeah ♪

30
00:01:29,156 --> 00:01:34,595
♪ Awaken it right now
with a miracle ♪

31
00:01:34,595 --> 00:01:37,531
♪ Vanguard, now we all become ♪

32
00:01:37,531 --> 00:01:41,935
♪ That burning red hot
blazing flame to the future,

33
00:01:41,935 --> 00:01:46,106
we'll keep on racing through ♪

34
00:01:46,106 --> 00:01:49,743
♪ Final turn ♪

35
00:01:49,743 --> 00:01:56,717
♪

36
00:02:04,091 --> 00:02:05,359
Having a good time?

37
00:02:05,359 --> 00:02:07,160
Huh‐‐yeah!

38
00:02:07,160 --> 00:02:09,830
‐Totally!
‐Hmm.

39
00:02:09,830 --> 00:02:13,300
'Cause when you walked in here
today, you looked kinda sad,

40
00:02:13,300 --> 00:02:16,770
like a girl had just
stood you up or something.

41
00:02:16,770 --> 00:02:18,805
(gasping)

42
00:02:18,805 --> 00:02:20,440
What‐‐no way!

43
00:02:20,440 --> 00:02:23,510
I just thought I saw Kai here!

44
00:02:23,510 --> 00:02:27,080
Yeah, you know, I haven't
seen him in a couple of days,

45
00:02:27,080 --> 00:02:29,916
but you never can
tell with that guy.

46
00:02:29,916 --> 00:02:32,552
Why do you wanna
see him so badly?

47
00:02:32,552 --> 00:02:33,920
Well, I was just hoping

48
00:02:33,920 --> 00:02:37,290
that I could have another
Vanguard fight with him.

49
00:02:39,159 --> 00:02:40,927
The first time we battled,

50
00:02:40,927 --> 00:02:43,530
I couldn't help but feel
like he was holding back a bit

51
00:02:43,530 --> 00:02:45,632
because I was new to the game.

52
00:02:45,632 --> 00:02:48,035
♪

53
00:02:48,035 --> 00:02:51,038
Since that day, I've had
a bunch of other battles.

54
00:02:51,038 --> 00:02:52,873
I know the rules pretty well,

55
00:02:52,873 --> 00:02:55,208
and I'm having a
lot of fun now, too!

56
00:02:55,208 --> 00:02:59,012
Plus, I might just be a
little better than I was.

57
00:02:59,012 --> 00:03:00,914
So I wanna fight Kai again,

58
00:03:00,914 --> 00:03:04,017
and show him he doesn't
have to take it easy on me.

59
00:03:05,452 --> 00:03:09,256
I think I just saw
a twinkle in your eye.

60
00:03:09,256 --> 00:03:11,358
That's always how
it is with new players.

61
00:03:11,358 --> 00:03:13,360
You're having so
much fun playing,

62
00:03:13,360 --> 00:03:16,963
you don't even care
whether you win or lose.

63
00:03:16,963 --> 00:03:19,066
Can I take a look at your deck?

64
00:03:19,066 --> 00:03:21,068
Uh, sure.

65
00:03:21,068 --> 00:03:24,838
♪

66
00:03:24,838 --> 00:03:27,040
Hmm.

67
00:03:27,040 --> 00:03:28,775
Is something wrong?

68
00:03:28,775 --> 00:03:31,244
Hmm‐‐here's the plan.

69
00:03:31,244 --> 00:03:32,679
Why don't you swing by the shop

70
00:03:32,679 --> 00:03:34,614
on your way home
from school tomorrow?

71
00:03:34,614 --> 00:03:37,651
I'll have a surprise
waiting for you.

72
00:03:37,651 --> 00:03:39,086
Really?

73
00:03:39,086 --> 00:03:42,622
Yeah, but you've
gotta come get it!

74
00:03:42,622 --> 00:03:44,124
Hmm.

75
00:03:44,124 --> 00:03:50,297
♪

76
00:03:50,297 --> 00:03:51,998
A surprise, surprise!

77
00:03:51,998 --> 00:03:54,401
Do you think it
could be a present?

78
00:03:54,401 --> 00:03:56,470
No clue‐‐I didn't even ask.

79
00:03:59,406 --> 00:04:01,942
‐We've arrived!
‐Huh?

80
00:04:01,942 --> 00:04:04,911
I hear you've got a
surprise of something.

81
00:04:04,911 --> 00:04:07,614
Well, how about you
share some of it with me?

82
00:04:07,614 --> 00:04:10,851
(meowing and yelling)

83
00:04:10,851 --> 00:04:14,254
Keep it down or get out.

84
00:04:14,254 --> 00:04:16,723
I'm glad you were
able to make it, Aichi.

85
00:04:16,723 --> 00:04:18,492
‐Thanks!
‐Card boss!

86
00:04:18,492 --> 00:04:22,028
What's the nice thing
you got for him, huh?

87
00:04:22,028 --> 00:04:23,964
Well, to figure that one out,

88
00:04:23,964 --> 00:04:26,666
you're gonna need to have
a Vanguard battle first.

89
00:04:26,666 --> 00:04:28,769
A card fight, huh?

90
00:04:28,769 --> 00:04:31,938
Yes, and once
that match it over,

91
00:04:31,938 --> 00:04:33,673
you'll understand
what the surprise is.

92
00:04:33,673 --> 00:04:35,475
Then count me in!

93
00:04:35,475 --> 00:04:38,145
I think you're good as is.

94
00:04:38,145 --> 00:04:40,781
It's Aichi that
really needs to see it.

95
00:04:40,781 --> 00:04:42,215
What's this about?

96
00:04:42,215 --> 00:04:45,619
You see, I was gonna have
a card fight with you myself,

97
00:04:45,619 --> 00:04:47,554
but we're getting a
new shipment of cards,

98
00:04:47,554 --> 00:04:49,356
and I have to go pick it up.

99
00:04:49,356 --> 00:04:53,293
So, in my place, I'd
like you to battle Misaki.

100
00:04:53,293 --> 00:04:55,495
(gasping)

101
00:04:57,030 --> 00:04:59,332
No, you can't be serious.

102
00:04:59,332 --> 00:05:02,569
I've gotta fight this guy?

103
00:05:02,569 --> 00:05:04,070
Yep, that's right!

104
00:05:04,070 --> 00:05:07,274
Uncle, you can't make me.

105
00:05:07,274 --> 00:05:08,909
It's "shop manager."

106
00:05:08,909 --> 00:05:11,344
Don't play games
with me, Uncle Shin.

107
00:05:11,344 --> 00:05:14,281
You know I've never had
a Vanguard battle before.

108
00:05:14,281 --> 00:05:15,582
(gasping)

109
00:05:15,582 --> 00:05:17,951
How could that be‐‐
you're here every day!

110
00:05:17,951 --> 00:05:20,887
I only work for Shin
to make some extra money.

111
00:05:20,887 --> 00:05:23,590
You think I care
about card fights, Uncle?

112
00:05:23,590 --> 00:05:26,026
It's "manager."

113
00:05:26,026 --> 00:05:27,694
I wonder if there really
is something special

114
00:05:27,694 --> 00:05:29,062
about this fight,

115
00:05:29,062 --> 00:05:31,498
or maybe you're just
messing with both of us.

116
00:05:31,498 --> 00:05:33,466
You'll only know if you try!

117
00:05:33,466 --> 00:05:35,669
And I'm not playing
any tricks, okay?

118
00:05:35,669 --> 00:05:36,703
Oh, no!

119
00:05:36,703 --> 00:05:39,573
I'm gonna be late
for the pick‐up!

120
00:05:39,573 --> 00:05:41,508
I made this deck for you.

121
00:05:41,508 --> 00:05:42,676
But...

122
00:05:42,676 --> 00:05:46,079
I'm sure you'll be
just fine, Misaki.

123
00:05:46,079 --> 00:05:49,983
Ohh‐‐well, what
about the shop, huh?

124
00:05:49,983 --> 00:05:51,952
While I'm having
this Vanguard fight,

125
00:05:51,952 --> 00:05:54,120
who's gonna watch
over the counter for us?

126
00:05:54,120 --> 00:05:55,422
Oh, yeah!

127
00:05:55,422 --> 00:05:57,023
In that case...

128
00:05:57,023 --> 00:06:01,127
♪

129
00:06:01,127 --> 00:06:04,130
use the Assisticat!

130
00:06:04,130 --> 00:06:05,332
Seriously?

131
00:06:07,701 --> 00:06:09,402
Yo, yo, yo!

132
00:06:11,538 --> 00:06:13,340
(meowing)

133
00:06:13,340 --> 00:06:15,442
♪

134
00:06:15,442 --> 00:06:18,745
What‐‐that manager
really said that?

135
00:06:18,745 --> 00:06:21,581
Yup, that's why they
both look so serious.

136
00:06:21,581 --> 00:06:23,383
Hmm.

137
00:06:23,383 --> 00:06:26,586
Then what's up with that guy?

138
00:06:26,586 --> 00:06:28,121
Can't you tell?

139
00:06:28,121 --> 00:06:29,990
Actually, no.

140
00:06:29,990 --> 00:06:32,158
I'm not gonna sit
around and let Aichi

141
00:06:32,158 --> 00:06:34,261
get something
amazing and not me.

142
00:06:34,261 --> 00:06:36,263
I have to make sure
that doesn't happen.

143
00:06:36,263 --> 00:06:39,332
Aichi, lose the fight!

144
00:06:39,332 --> 00:06:42,135
How dare you hog all
the nice stuff to yourself?

145
00:06:42,135 --> 00:06:45,038
Creepy guy.

146
00:06:45,038 --> 00:06:47,574
So it's this kind of deck.

147
00:06:47,574 --> 00:06:50,176
I wonder what Shin
is thinking, though.

148
00:06:50,176 --> 00:06:51,511
I need a day off with pay

149
00:06:51,511 --> 00:06:53,980
for putting up with
this little stunt.

150
00:06:53,980 --> 00:06:55,515
She's never had a fight before,

151
00:06:55,515 --> 00:06:59,119
so maybe I should
go a bit easy on her.

152
00:06:59,119 --> 00:07:01,388
‐Let's start.
‐Sure thing!

153
00:07:01,388 --> 00:07:03,823
♪

154
00:07:03,823 --> 00:07:06,860
(gasping)

155
00:07:06,860 --> 00:07:08,929
Sorry, let me shuffle again.

156
00:07:08,929 --> 00:07:10,764
Yeah.

157
00:07:10,764 --> 00:07:13,233
She's not used
to handling cards.

158
00:07:14,801 --> 00:07:17,003
Please, cut my deck.

159
00:07:17,003 --> 00:07:38,825
♪

160
00:07:38,825 --> 00:07:40,327
You have to picture it.

161
00:07:40,327 --> 00:07:42,028
All right.

162
00:07:42,028 --> 00:07:45,899
‐Vanguard, stand up now.
‐Vanguard, stand up now.

163
00:07:45,899 --> 00:07:47,701
Lozenge Magus.

164
00:07:49,336 --> 00:07:51,571
Stardust Trumpeter.

165
00:07:51,571 --> 00:08:04,250
♪

166
00:08:04,250 --> 00:08:06,619
I'll take first turn, okay?

167
00:08:06,619 --> 00:08:13,493
♪

168
00:08:13,493 --> 00:08:16,796
I ride the Oracle
Guardian Gemini.

169
00:08:16,796 --> 00:08:19,666
♪

170
00:08:19,666 --> 00:08:23,103
And I use the effect
of Lozenge Magus

171
00:08:23,103 --> 00:08:25,739
to slide her
into the rear‐guard.

172
00:08:27,173 --> 00:08:28,908
She is such a rookie!

173
00:08:28,908 --> 00:08:30,677
Check it out, you guys!

174
00:08:30,677 --> 00:08:32,812
Don't make me come over there.

175
00:08:32,812 --> 00:08:34,314
I'm sorry, ma'am!

176
00:08:34,314 --> 00:08:36,149
It's your turn.

177
00:08:41,688 --> 00:08:44,057
Ride, Little Sage, Marron!

178
00:08:44,057 --> 00:08:48,661
♪

179
00:08:48,661 --> 00:08:51,197
And I call Wingal and Flogal!

180
00:08:51,197 --> 00:08:53,400
♪

181
00:08:53,400 --> 00:08:55,335
I support Wingal with Flogal,

182
00:08:55,335 --> 00:08:57,704
and attack your Gemini!

183
00:08:57,704 --> 00:08:59,939
(growling)

184
00:08:59,939 --> 00:09:02,375
I check for a damaged trigger.

185
00:09:02,375 --> 00:09:06,446
♪

186
00:09:06,446 --> 00:09:09,049
Next, I attack
Gemini with Marron!

187
00:09:10,884 --> 00:09:12,952
Checking for a drive trigger.

188
00:09:12,952 --> 00:09:14,854
♪

189
00:09:14,854 --> 00:09:17,424
Got it‐‐try this on!

190
00:09:17,424 --> 00:09:20,693
Eponess Trigger grabs a
bonus 5,000 attack power.

191
00:09:20,693 --> 00:09:22,195
Thanks to the critical effect,

192
00:09:22,195 --> 00:09:24,998
the damage of this attack
just went up by one point!

193
00:09:24,998 --> 00:09:27,200
Another two damage, I believe?

194
00:09:27,200 --> 00:09:30,637
Then I can check for
two damaged triggers.

195
00:09:30,637 --> 00:09:33,206
I'm checking the first card‐‐

196
00:09:33,206 --> 00:09:35,642
I got it‐‐Draw Trigger.

197
00:09:35,642 --> 00:09:37,710
A Draw Trigger?

198
00:09:37,710 --> 00:09:41,114
When revealed, it allows
me to draw an extra card.

199
00:09:41,114 --> 00:09:43,283
♪

200
00:09:43,283 --> 00:09:46,953
Now, checking for
another Damage Trigger.

201
00:09:46,953 --> 00:09:48,588
Draw Trigger again.

202
00:09:48,588 --> 00:09:53,193
The ability to draw extra
cards, is that really helpful?

203
00:09:53,193 --> 00:09:55,628
That's three damage
on his first turn!

204
00:09:55,628 --> 00:09:58,465
Yeah, great way
to start the game!

205
00:09:58,465 --> 00:10:00,200
Huh?

206
00:10:00,200 --> 00:10:02,268
Curse him and his good luck!

207
00:10:02,268 --> 00:10:05,805
Just lose, all right?

208
00:10:05,805 --> 00:10:08,942
‐Hey, uh‐‐
‐Quiet!

209
00:10:08,942 --> 00:10:11,144
Sure, no prob!

210
00:10:11,144 --> 00:10:13,713
My turn now.

211
00:10:13,713 --> 00:10:15,815
I ride the Maiden of Libra.

212
00:10:22,922 --> 00:10:25,291
And I call two Silent Toms.

213
00:10:30,864 --> 00:10:33,333
I attack Marron with Silent Tom.

214
00:10:33,333 --> 00:10:35,435
I guard the attack with Flogal.

215
00:10:35,435 --> 00:10:37,170
Huh‐‐no, that won't work.

216
00:10:37,170 --> 00:10:38,972
‐Huh?
‐Silent Tom's skill

217
00:10:38,972 --> 00:10:40,640
prevents that.

218
00:10:40,640 --> 00:10:44,144
A grade zero unit
cannot guard his attack.

219
00:10:44,144 --> 00:10:45,879
Too bad.

220
00:10:45,879 --> 00:10:54,320
♪

221
00:10:54,320 --> 00:10:56,823
(gun firing and grunting)

222
00:10:58,358 --> 00:11:01,060
There are cards you
can't guard against?

223
00:11:01,060 --> 00:11:03,963
♪

224
00:11:03,963 --> 00:11:06,399
Misaki might never
have fought before,

225
00:11:06,399 --> 00:11:08,468
but she sure knows
what she's doing.

226
00:11:08,468 --> 00:11:10,136
I've gotta be more careful.

227
00:11:10,136 --> 00:11:12,605
That's a strong unit.

228
00:11:12,605 --> 00:11:14,174
You go, girl!

229
00:11:14,174 --> 00:11:16,242
Beat that puny little wimp!

230
00:11:16,242 --> 00:11:17,544
Get a life.

231
00:11:17,544 --> 00:11:18,912
I'm fighting here.

232
00:11:18,912 --> 00:11:20,647
Ah, don't hurt me!

233
00:11:20,647 --> 00:11:22,382
(laughing)

234
00:11:22,382 --> 00:11:31,424
♪

235
00:11:34,894 --> 00:11:39,399
♪

236
00:11:40,633 --> 00:11:49,609
♪

237
00:11:49,609 --> 00:11:51,811
I'm still ahead
in terms of damage,

238
00:11:51,811 --> 00:11:55,014
but I have to do something
about those Silent Toms!

239
00:11:55,014 --> 00:11:56,849
It's my turn!

240
00:12:00,086 --> 00:12:02,222
Yes!

241
00:12:02,222 --> 00:12:04,591
Arise now, my avatar,

242
00:12:04,591 --> 00:12:07,727
and ride Blaster Blade!

243
00:12:07,727 --> 00:12:13,366
♪

244
00:12:13,366 --> 00:12:16,703
You're not gonna get up
from this counterblast.

245
00:12:16,703 --> 00:12:19,606
I retire one of
your Silent Toms.

246
00:12:19,606 --> 00:12:28,147
♪

247
00:12:28,147 --> 00:12:30,250
Good, that's one down.

248
00:12:30,250 --> 00:12:33,086
I call forth
Flogal and Gallatin!

249
00:12:33,086 --> 00:12:36,289
♪

250
00:12:36,289 --> 00:12:39,292
I use Gallatin to attack
your Maiden of Libra!

251
00:12:39,292 --> 00:12:42,095
Oracle Guardian Nike disagrees.

252
00:12:42,095 --> 00:12:46,566
♪

253
00:12:46,566 --> 00:12:49,402
Next up, using
the support of Flogal,

254
00:12:49,402 --> 00:12:52,238
I'll have Blaster Blade
attack your Vanguard!

255
00:12:52,238 --> 00:12:53,906
Drive check!

256
00:12:53,906 --> 00:12:57,543
♪

257
00:12:57,543 --> 00:12:59,746
You sure like attacking.

258
00:12:59,746 --> 00:13:01,814
Draw Trigger.

259
00:13:01,814 --> 00:13:04,250
(grunting)

260
00:13:04,250 --> 00:13:06,753
I draw another
card thanks to you.

261
00:13:06,753 --> 00:13:09,756
♪

262
00:13:09,756 --> 00:13:12,325
Big mistake.

263
00:13:12,325 --> 00:13:15,028
I combine the power
of Wingal and Flogal

264
00:13:15,028 --> 00:13:17,430
to attack your Silent Tom!

265
00:13:17,430 --> 00:13:19,265
(growling)

266
00:13:19,265 --> 00:13:22,669
♪

267
00:13:22,669 --> 00:13:26,272
All right, both Silent
Toms are in the drop zone!

268
00:13:26,272 --> 00:13:28,341
I wouldn't celebrate yet.

269
00:13:29,542 --> 00:13:31,577
We're just getting started.

270
00:13:37,083 --> 00:13:39,252
No way.

271
00:13:39,252 --> 00:13:41,921
Beautiful goddess
of radiant light,

272
00:13:41,921 --> 00:13:45,425
ride CEO Amaterasu.

273
00:13:45,425 --> 00:13:53,166
♪

274
00:13:53,166 --> 00:13:55,368
Wow, man, grade three!

275
00:13:55,368 --> 00:13:57,337
I think Aichi's
in trouble, guys.

276
00:13:57,337 --> 00:13:59,706
That's one of the
strongest cards in the game!

277
00:13:59,706 --> 00:14:00,940
A grade three!

278
00:14:00,940 --> 00:14:03,976
Boy, you're crazy about
those grade threes, aren't ya?

279
00:14:03,976 --> 00:14:06,446
Of course, they're
strong just like me.

280
00:14:06,446 --> 00:14:08,047
Yeah, right.

281
00:14:08,047 --> 00:14:10,650
♪

282
00:14:10,650 --> 00:14:15,088
‐A grade three?
‐Amaterasu's special ability.

283
00:14:15,088 --> 00:14:17,757
I add the top card of
my deck to her soul stack,

284
00:14:17,757 --> 00:14:20,860
and now I can look
at the top of my deck.

285
00:14:20,860 --> 00:14:23,096
Check the top card?

286
00:14:23,096 --> 00:14:25,365
I get to preview the next card,

287
00:14:25,365 --> 00:14:26,999
then I can leave it on top,

288
00:14:26,999 --> 00:14:29,802
or I can put it on
the bottom of my deck.

289
00:14:29,802 --> 00:14:32,405
How, exactly, is that
supposed to help you?

290
00:14:32,405 --> 00:14:35,074
Oh, you'll see.

291
00:14:35,074 --> 00:14:37,510
I don't need this.

292
00:14:37,510 --> 00:14:40,413
I call two Oracle
Guardian Wiseman out,

293
00:14:40,413 --> 00:14:42,048
and a Gemini, too.

294
00:14:42,048 --> 00:14:45,385
♪

295
00:14:45,385 --> 00:14:47,653
Wiseman is attacking
Blaster Blade.

296
00:14:47,653 --> 00:14:49,522
I guard with Epona!

297
00:14:50,823 --> 00:14:53,793
And now a Wiseman with
the support of a Gemini

298
00:14:53,793 --> 00:14:56,429
attacking your Vanguard again.

299
00:14:56,429 --> 00:14:58,965
I'll do a damage trigger check.

300
00:14:58,965 --> 00:15:01,768
Great, it's a Heal Trigger!

301
00:15:01,768 --> 00:15:03,736
As you know, Elaine's
effect allows me

302
00:15:03,736 --> 00:15:05,905
to recover one card
from the damage zone.

303
00:15:05,905 --> 00:15:08,408
Uh‐uh‐‐you can't.

304
00:15:08,408 --> 00:15:10,276
The heal effect only triggers

305
00:15:10,276 --> 00:15:13,579
if you have more cards in your
damage zone than you opponent.

306
00:15:13,579 --> 00:15:17,884
♪

307
00:15:17,884 --> 00:15:20,586
Oh, no, what a waste!

308
00:15:20,586 --> 00:15:23,055
I think this girl knows more
about the cards and rules

309
00:15:23,055 --> 00:15:27,627
than most of us guys, and
it's her very first fight!

310
00:15:27,627 --> 00:15:29,862
I spend eight hours
a day in this shop

311
00:15:29,862 --> 00:15:31,898
watching all of you play.

312
00:15:31,898 --> 00:15:34,901
I've pretty much
had to learn them.

313
00:15:34,901 --> 00:15:36,769
Besides, I need
to know the rules

314
00:15:36,769 --> 00:15:39,105
in order to serve our customers.

315
00:15:39,105 --> 00:15:43,176
I see‐‐well, that explains
why you're so good, Misaki.

316
00:15:43,176 --> 00:15:46,412
But I still gain an
effect off that trigger.

317
00:15:46,412 --> 00:15:49,348
Blaster Blade's power
goes up by 5,000!

318
00:15:49,348 --> 00:15:51,684
♪

319
00:15:51,684 --> 00:15:54,787
That should stop her attacks.

320
00:15:54,787 --> 00:15:58,658
I attack Blaster
Blade with Amaterasu.

321
00:15:58,658 --> 00:16:00,226
But why?

322
00:16:03,162 --> 00:16:07,133
You see, my Vanguard
has Twin Drive.

323
00:16:07,133 --> 00:16:09,268
And what's that?

324
00:16:09,268 --> 00:16:11,704
All grade three cards
have a special ability

325
00:16:11,704 --> 00:16:13,606
that's called Twin Drive.

326
00:16:13,606 --> 00:16:15,241
Instead of drawing
one drive trigger,

327
00:16:15,241 --> 00:16:17,777
you draw two.

328
00:16:17,777 --> 00:16:19,378
First check...

329
00:16:19,378 --> 00:16:20,446
no.

330
00:16:22,048 --> 00:16:24,417
Second check?

331
00:16:24,417 --> 00:16:26,385
That was lucky.

332
00:16:26,385 --> 00:16:27,887
Are you relieved?

333
00:16:27,887 --> 00:16:31,023
Amaterasu has
another little ability.

334
00:16:31,023 --> 00:16:32,825
If I have at least
four cards in my hand,

335
00:16:32,825 --> 00:16:35,595
her power goes up by 4,000.

336
00:16:35,595 --> 00:16:37,330
You have five!

337
00:16:37,330 --> 00:16:42,301
I see‐‐so that's why your
deck has so many draw triggers!

338
00:16:42,301 --> 00:16:45,571
You were activating
Amaterasu's ability!

339
00:16:45,571 --> 00:16:48,508
A bit late for that realization.

340
00:16:48,508 --> 00:16:49,809
Hmm.

341
00:16:49,809 --> 00:16:57,550
♪

342
00:16:57,550 --> 00:17:00,086
(yelling)

343
00:17:00,086 --> 00:17:02,288
♪

344
00:17:02,288 --> 00:17:04,524
I don't like the look
of this one bit, guys!

345
00:17:04,524 --> 00:17:08,995
I need to get myself a
copy of that grade three!

346
00:17:08,995 --> 00:17:11,597
My turn now.

347
00:17:11,597 --> 00:17:14,700
I'll have Wingal and
Flogal switch places,

348
00:17:14,700 --> 00:17:17,803
then I retire Flogal
and call in Gallatin!

349
00:17:17,803 --> 00:17:22,241
♪

350
00:17:22,241 --> 00:17:25,177
Gallatin attacks your Vanguard!

351
00:17:25,177 --> 00:17:26,646
Whatever.

352
00:17:26,646 --> 00:17:29,649
♪

353
00:17:29,649 --> 00:17:33,986
Almost there‐‐and now I have
Flogal supporting Blaster Blade

354
00:17:33,986 --> 00:17:36,155
to attack Amaterasu.

355
00:17:36,155 --> 00:17:39,125
Chocolat guards,
activate ability.

356
00:17:39,125 --> 00:17:42,361
I send an Oracle Guardian card
from my hand to the drop zone

357
00:17:42,361 --> 00:17:43,829
to cancel your attack.

358
00:17:43,829 --> 00:17:47,433
♪

359
00:17:47,433 --> 00:17:49,368
That attack is over.

360
00:17:49,368 --> 00:17:52,805
♪

361
00:17:52,805 --> 00:17:55,174
My card hits the drop zone.

362
00:17:55,174 --> 00:17:57,209
I'll do a drive trigger check!

363
00:17:57,209 --> 00:17:59,545
Critical effect acquired!

364
00:17:59,545 --> 00:18:03,149
That's an extra 5,000
attack power for Gallatin!

365
00:18:03,149 --> 00:18:05,484
Now I support him
with the power of Wingal

366
00:18:05,484 --> 00:18:07,486
and attack Amaterasu!

367
00:18:09,355 --> 00:18:10,923
I guard it.

368
00:18:14,961 --> 00:18:17,129
(gun firing and shrieking)

369
00:18:19,799 --> 00:18:21,133
No way!

370
00:18:21,133 --> 00:18:23,135
Let's finish this game.

371
00:18:23,135 --> 00:18:25,338
I activate Amaterasu's skill.

372
00:18:25,338 --> 00:18:27,139
I charge her soul stack,

373
00:18:27,139 --> 00:18:29,308
and I check the top card.

374
00:18:29,308 --> 00:18:32,244
Hmm‐‐that one's useless.

375
00:18:33,446 --> 00:18:35,948
I call Miracle Kid and Cocoa.

376
00:18:35,948 --> 00:18:40,586
♪

377
00:18:40,586 --> 00:18:43,155
Cocoa is another unit that
allows me to take a look

378
00:18:43,155 --> 00:18:46,092
at the top card of my deck.

379
00:18:46,092 --> 00:18:47,593
Hmm.

380
00:18:47,593 --> 00:18:49,562
That can stay.

381
00:18:49,562 --> 00:18:52,531
I support Wiseman with
the power of Miracle Kid

382
00:18:52,531 --> 00:18:54,767
and attack Blaster Blade.

383
00:18:54,767 --> 00:18:56,802
Epona to guard!

384
00:18:56,802 --> 00:18:59,205
Your attacks won't get me.

385
00:18:59,205 --> 00:19:03,209
Supporting Wiseman
with Gemini, attack.

386
00:19:03,209 --> 00:19:05,111
I guard with Epona!

387
00:19:05,111 --> 00:19:07,279
Amaterasu now has
the support of Cocoa

388
00:19:07,279 --> 00:19:09,015
and is attacking your Vanguard.

389
00:19:09,015 --> 00:19:11,183
Amaterasu?

390
00:19:11,183 --> 00:19:13,786
Oh, no, I used up all my cards!

391
00:19:13,786 --> 00:19:18,758
♪

392
00:19:18,758 --> 00:19:20,660
Now for her Twin Drive.

393
00:19:20,660 --> 00:19:22,161
Let's see.

394
00:19:22,161 --> 00:19:24,130
First check.

395
00:19:24,130 --> 00:19:26,298
Look, this is it.

396
00:19:28,367 --> 00:19:31,771
That's the card she left on top.

397
00:19:31,771 --> 00:19:34,206
The purpose of me checking
the top card of my deck

398
00:19:34,206 --> 00:19:36,809
is to set myself up
with a drive trigger,

399
00:19:36,809 --> 00:19:40,112
and to use it against you
at a critical time like this.

400
00:19:41,914 --> 00:19:43,916
Drive trigger activated.

401
00:19:43,916 --> 00:19:47,586
Nike's effect adds 5,000
to Amaterasu's power.

402
00:19:47,586 --> 00:19:49,722
The damage is up by one as well.

403
00:19:49,722 --> 00:19:53,693
♪

404
00:19:53,693 --> 00:19:55,861
Second check.

405
00:19:55,861 --> 00:20:01,701
No trigger, but Amaterasu's
power is already 22,000.

406
00:20:01,701 --> 00:20:04,203
This is the power
of grade three units.

407
00:20:04,203 --> 00:20:06,539
♪

408
00:20:06,539 --> 00:20:09,108
So, if your deck doesn't
have anything better

409
00:20:09,108 --> 00:20:10,943
than a grade two unit,

410
00:20:10,943 --> 00:20:13,713
well, you're doomed to fail.

411
00:20:13,713 --> 00:20:18,417
♪

412
00:20:18,417 --> 00:20:21,320
(yelling)

413
00:20:21,320 --> 00:20:26,826
♪

414
00:20:28,928 --> 00:20:31,030
Good game!

415
00:20:31,030 --> 00:20:34,366
It worked‐‐he lost.

416
00:20:34,366 --> 00:20:36,035
(sighing)

417
00:20:40,106 --> 00:20:42,041
I need some better cards!

418
00:20:42,041 --> 00:20:44,677
Blaster Blade isn't
enough on his own.

419
00:20:49,715 --> 00:20:52,685
So you lost to Misaki, eh?

420
00:20:52,685 --> 00:20:53,719
Yes.

421
00:20:53,719 --> 00:20:57,056
Did you find
anything surprising?

422
00:20:57,056 --> 00:20:58,257
I did.

423
00:20:58,257 --> 00:21:01,360
I saw that there are still a
lot of things I need to learn.

424
00:21:01,360 --> 00:21:05,631
Vanguard is much bigger and
more complicated than I thought.

425
00:21:05,631 --> 00:21:07,099
That was the special thing

426
00:21:07,099 --> 00:21:09,568
that I wanted you to
see with your own eyes.

427
00:21:09,568 --> 00:21:11,070
Huh?

428
00:21:11,070 --> 00:21:12,838
We all started
like you, you know‐‐

429
00:21:12,838 --> 00:21:14,840
super eager to be
playing the game

430
00:21:14,840 --> 00:21:17,943
and yet only knowing
a bit about it.

431
00:21:17,943 --> 00:21:20,312
That's not how you
get better, though.

432
00:21:21,647 --> 00:21:24,550
And you're not gonna defeat
Kai that way, are you?

433
00:21:25,885 --> 00:21:27,219
Glad you saw it.

434
00:21:27,219 --> 00:21:29,355
That's a big step today!

435
00:21:29,355 --> 00:21:32,291
Vanguard means a
lot to that kid, eh?

436
00:21:32,291 --> 00:21:35,394
Ha‐‐I learned way
more from that battle.

437
00:21:35,394 --> 00:21:37,530
Now that I know, I can
make some plans, too!

438
00:21:37,530 --> 00:21:39,832
And what exactly did
you learn from that fight?

439
00:21:39,832 --> 00:21:42,001
Oh, not much.

440
00:21:43,569 --> 00:21:46,105
Only that there's another
awesome grade three unit

441
00:21:46,105 --> 00:21:48,474
I need to get for my deck!

442
00:21:48,474 --> 00:21:50,009
(laughing)

443
00:21:50,009 --> 00:21:51,477
Please say you're kidding.

444
00:21:51,477 --> 00:21:53,379
If you have
questions about cards,

445
00:21:53,379 --> 00:21:55,815
I'll always be happy
to answer them for you.

446
00:21:55,815 --> 00:21:59,318
As long as he keeps
playing here, right?

447
00:21:59,318 --> 00:22:01,520
(laughing)

448
00:22:01,520 --> 00:22:03,189
Thank you very much.

449
00:22:03,189 --> 00:22:05,224
♪

450
00:22:05,224 --> 00:22:09,929
Grade threes, and all those
cards I've never seen before!

451
00:22:09,929 --> 00:22:14,266
I want to know more about
Vanguard and get even stronger

452
00:22:14,266 --> 00:22:18,370
so the next time I face Kai...

453
00:22:18,370 --> 00:22:20,105
mmm.

454
00:22:20,105 --> 00:22:23,509
♪

455
00:22:26,812 --> 00:22:35,020
♪

456
00:22:35,020 --> 00:22:37,723
♪ I feel the sunshine
lighting up the sky ♪

457
00:22:37,723 --> 00:22:40,659
♪ The sea, the horizon,
feeling so alive ♪

458
00:22:40,659 --> 00:22:46,165
♪ Yes, I have never
felt this way before ♪

459
00:22:46,165 --> 00:22:48,901
♪ The stars in the sky
are glowing just for me ♪

460
00:22:48,901 --> 00:22:51,804
♪ The wind, I've been waiting,
is here and I believe ♪

461
00:22:51,804 --> 00:22:54,373
♪ Now's the time,
and I will fly ♪

462
00:22:54,373 --> 00:22:56,642
♪ I see the "go" sign ♪

463
00:22:56,642 --> 00:22:59,245
♪ Take a chance‐‐yes, no? ♪

464
00:22:59,245 --> 00:23:01,113
♪ I can see my
hopes and dreams ♪

465
00:23:01,113 --> 00:23:03,048
♪ I'll fight until the end ♪

466
00:23:03,048 --> 00:23:06,151
♪ Just believe, you will see ♪

467
00:23:06,151 --> 00:23:11,390
♪ It's time to show
the fire burning in me ♪

468
00:23:11,390 --> 00:23:15,160
♪ Fly away, fly far away ♪

469
00:23:15,160 --> 00:23:18,030
♪ Blasting rockets to the sky ♪

470
00:23:18,030 --> 00:23:20,833
♪ We will soar our way up high ♪

471
00:23:20,833 --> 00:23:22,468
♪ Let's go together ♪

472
00:23:22,468 --> 00:23:26,372
♪ Catch my star, yes, I can ♪

473
00:23:26,372 --> 00:23:29,208
♪ It's the moment of our lives ♪

474
00:23:29,208 --> 00:23:32,278
♪ Our passion burning
blazing bright ♪

475
00:23:32,278 --> 00:23:37,049
♪ Never giving up, I trust
my heart, now I believe ♪

476
00:23:37,049 --> 00:23:39,618
♪ Yes, we can reach our dreams ♪

477
00:23:39,618 --> 00:23:44,023
♪ Together we'll
create new miracles ♪

478
00:23:44,023 --> 00:23:46,892
♪ A beautiful world ♪

479
00:23:46,892 --> 00:23:49,495
♪ Now is the time ♪

480
00:23:49,495 --> 00:23:52,064
♪ We are ready to fight ♪

481
00:23:52,064 --> 00:23:56,135
♪ What are you waiting for‐‐
we are Dream Shooters ♪

482
00:24:00,539 --> 00:24:03,142
It was your first fight, Misaki?

483
00:24:03,142 --> 00:24:05,778
Yeah, but I'm always watching
them from the counter.

484
00:24:05,778 --> 00:24:06,812
Wow.

485
00:24:06,812 --> 00:24:08,347
Well, I was just happy
to play with someone

486
00:24:08,347 --> 00:24:10,015
as good as you.

487
00:24:10,015 --> 00:24:12,084
I bet there are lots of
strong people out there

488
00:24:12,084 --> 00:24:13,285
I haven't met yet!

489
00:24:13,285 --> 00:24:15,187
There's a powerful
grade‐schooler, you know.

490
00:24:15,187 --> 00:24:17,156
Oh, really‐‐I'd
like to meet him!

491
00:24:17,156 --> 00:24:20,559
Wait, is grade‐school kid
fighting Misaki right now?

492
00:24:20,559 --> 00:24:22,227
♪

493
00:24:22,227 --> 00:24:23,929
Next time, Whirlwind!

494
00:24:23,929 --> 00:24:25,965
Kamui, the Grade‐School Fighter!

495
00:24:25,965 --> 00:24:28,434
Picture it, myself
becoming stronger!

